Text: How does a external condom work?

A condom is a stretchy piece of latex or other kind of film that a guy covers his penis during sex. It works to catch and trap fluids - like pre cum and semen - so that they don’t enter the vagina, butt, or even mouth if you’re giving head. It’s a great form of birth control to prevent pregnancy and the ONLY way to prevent STDs.
